ＨＥＩＲＥＳＳ  ＯＦ  ＤＵＮＥＳ 

Time as a sculptor, a ceaseless artist who moulds rivers into deserts, glaciers to rain, gravel to dunes. 

Of those dunes and time, I am an heiress. This land and all its mystical music is my legacy - to hold, to revel in and to grow from, vein by vein, dune by dune. 

No form, no being stays the same for any fraction of time. It is out of wonder for that eternal, continuous change, Heiress of Dunes emerges.

“91% of plastic isn't recycled and millions of tons of plastic ends up becoming trash and litter, eventually ending up in the ocean. Through the collection, we aim to minimise our waste and take a step towards a relatively sustainable fashionscape.” @ggpanther . 

Made with precision we have used fabrics created with wrappers of crisps and biscuits, plastic bottles and other daily consumables that have been excavated from oceans & landfills and employed to create a chunk of the collection.

Gaurav Gupta Couture 2021-22 is inspired by the Universe. The expanse of the cosmos, the millions of stars, the axis and the movement of all planets; sprinkling and spiralling in infinite loops of time, meteoric showers and racing comets inspire abstract galactic embroideries and silhouettes. The garments exude a sense of expanse and grandeur of the cosmos. All done to strive -perfect harmony and love.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Gaurav Gupta For #VogueWeddingShow
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
'Gaurav Gupta Groom’ 

GG Groom conjures an attitude that is methodical and conceptual. State-of the-art bandhgalas, suits, sleek tuxedos and tailored trousers turned out in classic black and white suiting and luxurious velvet. Slight deconstruction highlights the structured silhouettes; explore details in the contrast sculpted lapels, wing collared shirts, angular peak lapels and celestial glass bugle bead embroidery. The designs stir a touch of fantasy and playfulness into traditional men’s wardrobe staples—contrast thread embroidery is engineered into mystical pegasus and panthers that look almost life-like.

Tap the link in bio to book an appointment.

@vogueindia

Across the Flame | Paris Couture Week SS ‘25

Glam look 1
Scripted on the face, a ‘shloka’ from the Bhagvad Gita Chapter 2, Verse 47: 
कर्मण्येवाधिकारस्ते मा फलेषु कदाचन।
मा कर्मफलहेतुर्भूर्मा ते सङ्गोऽस्त्वकर्मणि॥
“You have the right to perform your duty (karma) only, but never to its fruits.
Let not the fruits of action be your motive, nor let your attachment be to inaction.”

Glam Look 2
Wrapped in a celestial fever dream, crystals on the face represent a tryst with the cosmic universe.

Glam Look 3
Inspired by the presence of star-seeds, ‘children of the stars, rising from stardust and divine light’.

Glam Look 4
A celestial third eye sun adorns the forehead of the creatures, aligned with the third eye chakra ‘Ajna’ on the body.
